library(bayesplot)  ## 
rstan_options(auto_write = TRUE)  ## 
options(mc.cores = parallel::detectCores())  ## 
options(max.print = 99999)  ## 

schools_dat <- list(J = 8, y = c(28, 8, -3, 7, -1, 1, 18, 12), sigma = c(15, 
    10, 16, 11, 9, 11, 10, 18))

Stan model

Stan

data {
  int<lower=0> J;
  real y[J];
  real<lower=0> sigma[J];
}

parameters {
  real mu;
  real<lower=0> tau;
  real eta[J];
}

transformed parameters {
  real theta[J];
  for (j in 1:J)
    theta[j] = mu + tau * eta[j];
}

model {
  target += normal_lpdf(eta | 0, 1);
  target += normal_lpdf(y | theta, sigma);
}

model.stanR

model <- stan_model("model.stan")

Stan

Stan

fit <- sampling(object = model, data = schools_dat, iter = 1000, chains = 4)

## (8shcool.stan)

J <- 10

set.seed(1234)
eta <- rnorm(J, 0, 1)
mu <- 7.5  ## 
tau <- 6.3  ##  
sigma <- abs(rnorm(J, 0, 1))
theta <- NULL
y <- NULL
for (j in 1:J) {
    theta[j] <- mu + tau * eta[j]
    y[j] <- rnorm(1, theta[j], sigma[j])
}
true <- c(mu, tau, eta, theta)

## Stan data 
schools_dat <- list(J = J, y = y, sigma = sigma)

## (8shcool.stan)

J <- 10

set.seed(1234)
eta <- rnorm(J, 0, 1)
mu <- 7.5  ## 
tau <- 6.3  ##  
sigma <- abs(rnorm(J, 0, 1))
theta <- NULL
y <- NULL
for (j in 1:J) {
    theta[j] <- mu + tau * eta[j]
    y[j] <- rnorm(1, theta[j], sigma[j])
}
true <- c(mu, tau, eta, theta)

## Stan data 
schools_dat <- list(J = J, y = y, sigma = sigma)

## stan (Model)
fit <- sampling(object = model, data = schools_dat, iter = 1000, chains = 4)

##  ##
fit

## true()
matfit <- as.matrix(fit)

## 
mcmc_recover_intervals(matfit[, -ncol(matfit)], true)  ## fit'lp__'
